title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1978-10-22
lineage: Nakamichi CR3A w/ Dolby > Audigy 4 Pro @ 24/44.1 > Editing with NERO > Tracked With CD Wave > Dithered to 16 bit with Audacity > Flac (level 8).
description:
Set 1

Ollin Arrageed*-> Deal, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Peggy-O, Jack Straw

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, From The Heart Of Me, I Need A Miracle, Drums**-> Not Fade Away***-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks) Jam***-> I Got My Mojo Workin Jam***-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad***, E: Johnny B. Goode

*W Hamza El Din, **W Lee Oskar, ***W John Cippolina

reviews.review_text: stopped the jam to type this is a grate pull! Thank You! I love the sound of this room. lotsa hiss tho, sounds a few gen deep or something. thats why 3.5 stars( and ya never hype em up to 5)

Tape Hiss? First of all there is very little hiss on this recording. That guy who can't spell, probably had his eq jacked up or something. Just like the 20th and 21st, this is the best sounding aud source for this show. Upgrade on the Holwein source. Neat show, again the first set is great with Hamza. Set 2 pre drums lacks a bit after Fire, but from drums on is great.
